ZCZC GE58
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 262300 UTC
AT THE START OF THE PERIOD LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO BE
CENTRED JUST S OF ICELAND 993. IT WILL REMAIN SLOW MOV
FOR MUCH OF WEDNESDAY BEFORE MOV SLWY SE TO LIE TO THE
NW OF SCOTLAND 992 BY THURSDAY EVENING. THE LOW WILL
REMAIN SLOW MOV THROUGH FRIDAY. ON TUESDAY EVENING A
SMALL LOW 1003 OVER THE SW OF ENGLAND WILL MOV NEWARDS
AND FILL OVER THE N SEA BY WEDNESDAY MORNING. ON
WEDNESDAY A NEW DEVELOPING LOW WILL MOV QCKY NE FM THE S
OF SHANNON INTO IRISH SEA AND THEN ACROSS INTO THE N
SEA 998 BY MIDNIGHT THURSDAY. THE LOW THEN MOVS TO LIE
OVER SCANDINAVIA ON THURSDAY EVENING. STRG WINDS ARE EXP
TO DEVELOP ACROSS CULLERCOATS OVERNIGHT ON TUESDAY INTO
WEDNESDAY WITH A RISK OF GALES THROUGH THE ENGLISH
CHANNEL. STRG MAINLY SW WINDS WILL CONTINUE FOR MUCH OF
THE PERIOD WITH A FURTHER RISK OF SW GALES ACROSS SERN
AREAS ON THURSDAY
